  <h2> Frequently Asked Questions</h2>





  <div class="glass-card">


    <p style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 4px;">Q: Is Phantom safe for holding large amounts of meme coins?</p>


    <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">A: No. Phantom is a <strong>hot wallet</strong> - it's connected to the internet and vulnerable to browser exploits, phishing, and clipboard malware. Use it for trading only. Store the majority of your holdings in a hardware wallet like Ledger or Trezor.</p>





    <p style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 4px;">Q: Can I recover my funds if I lose my Ledger?</p>


    <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">A: Yes - you can recover your funds using your 24-word seed phrase on any compatible wallet (Ledger, Trezor, or even a software wallet in emergency). The device itself doesn't hold your crypto - the seed phrase does. This is why seed phrase security is more important than device security.</p>





    <p style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 4px;">Q: What's the best 2FA method for crypto exchanges?</p>


    <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">A: A YubiKey 5 NFC using FIDO2/WebAuthn. It's phishing-resistant - even if a fake website looks identical, the YubiKey won't authenticate. Google Authenticator is second-best. Avoid SMS 2FA due to SIM swap attacks.</p>





    <p style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 4px;">Q: How often should I revoke Solana token approvals?</p>


    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">A: At least once a month. Set a recurring calendar reminder. Use <code>revoke.cash</code> or Phantom/Backpack's built-in approval manager. Revoke any dApp you haven't used in 30+ days.</p>


  </div>





